snippet.textDisplay:
Humble Bundle suing Valve for that reasons is stupid on so many levels I don't even know which one I'd pick to make them realize how dumb that lawsuit is.

Despite them profiting off selling Steam keys bundles for YEARS, they call out Valve for "locking you into the system with monopolistic practices" without considering that Valve:

- takes the same 30% cut as most stores
- has been providing the better platform for years
- gives a HUGE base of potential customers to everyone who publishes on Steam
- made some small indie teams/solo devs rich because of this big customer base
- has always been great to modders, both those making full games(see Counter Strike, Icefrog with Dota 2 or Dota Autochess to name a couple) and those making items for them(TF2 hats, Dota 2 items, CS maps where they took the original map makers to work with them in some cases)

Last, but not least, Valve has been pushing Linux gaming BIG TIME by working on Proton making some games Linux compatible without the dev doing basicaly ANYTHING increasing their potential customer base, allowing more people to enjoy gaming on an OS that just a few years back was considered a no-go for gaming...

...I mean, are the guys at Humble Bundle serious or they're just hopping onto the "let's sue big stores because they're all evil!" bandwagon?
